## How to Convert DOCX to EPUB without Losing Formatting

Microsoft Word's DOCX format and EPUB are built on fundamentally different philosophies. Word is a WYSIWYG document editor; EPUB is a reflowable ebook standard. Converting between them requires understanding what transfers cleanly and what doesn't.

This guide walks you through converting DOCX to EPUB with maximum formatting preservation.

---

## Why DOCX to EPUB?

EPUB is the standard format for ebooks. If you've written a book, manual, or long-form document in Word, converting it to EPUB lets readers enjoy it on any ereader or reading app with a comfortable, adaptive reading experience.

The alternative — sending someone a DOCX — requires Word or a compatible editor. EPUB opens on Kindle (with conversion), Kobo, Apple Books, Google Play Books, and dozens of other apps.

---

## What Formatting Transfers from DOCX to EPUB?

Understanding what survives the conversion helps you **prepare your DOCX before converting** — which is the single biggest factor in quality.

### ✅ What Transfers Well

| Formatting | How It Transfers |
|-----------|-----------------|
| Headings (H1–H6) | Mapped to EPUB heading tags, generates Table of Contents |
| Paragraphs | Preserved as block elements |
| Bold, italic, underline | Preserved |
| Ordered and unordered lists | Preserved (may need verification in output) |
| Links/hyperlinks | Preserved as clickable links |
| Images (inline) | Preserved if embedded in DOCX; external links may break |
| Horizontal rules | Preserved |

### ⚠️ What Transfers Imperfectly

| Formatting | Issue |
|-----------|-------|
| Multi-column layouts | Collapse to single column in EPUB |
| Text boxes | May be lost or repositioned |
| Tables | Basic tables transfer; complex nested tables may break |
| Page breaks | EPUB uses flow-based breaks, not fixed pages |
| Headers and footers | Not typically rendered in EPUB readers |
| Track changes / comments | Not transferred |
| Custom fonts | May fall back to reader's default font |
| Watermarks | Not transferred |

### ❌ What Doesn't Transfer

- Macros and VBA code
- Fill-in form fields
- Embedded Excel/Word objects (OLE)
- Some complex WordArt and effects
- Fixed page numbers (EPUB uses flow-based content)

