## How to Prepare Your DOCX Before Converting

**This is the most important step.** Cleaning up your DOCX before conversion dramatically improves the EPUB output.

### 1. Use Heading Styles, Not Manual Formatting

❌ **Don't** manually make text bold and large to simulate a heading.

✅ **Do** apply Word's built-in Heading 1, Heading 2, etc. styles.

EPUB converters detect Heading styles to build the Table of Contents. Manual formatting is invisible to them.

### 2. Keep Lists as Word Lists

❌ **Don't** simulate lists using dashes, asterisks, or manual tabs.

✅ **Do** use Word's bullet point and numbered list tools.

Native Word lists convert cleanly to EPUB `<ul>` and `<ol>` elements.

### 3. Embed Images in the Document

If your DOCX references images by file path (e.g., "see image on page 3"), those images won't appear in the EPUB unless they're embedded in the DOCX file.

✅ **Insert images directly into the Word document** using Insert → Pictures.

### 4. Simplify Tables

Complex nested tables (tables inside tables, merged cells, diagonal cells) often break in EPUB conversion.

✅ **Keep tables simple:** single-level grids with clear row and column headers.

If your document has complex tables, consider converting them to plain text or simplifying the structure before conversion.

### 5. Remove Page Headers and Footers

EPUB readers don't render Word-style headers and footers consistently. They may be dropped or placed unpredictably.

✅ **Move important footer content** (e.g., page numbers, book title) into the main document body, or accept that they'll be omitted.

### 6. Avoid Text Boxes

Text boxes in Word don't convert well to EPUB. The text inside may be lost or repositioned.

✅ **Convert text boxes to regular paragraphs** or remove them.

### 7. Check Your Fonts

Custom fonts embedded in your DOCX may not render in all EPUB readers. EPUBs fall back to the reader's default serif or sans-serif font.

✅ **Use standard fonts** (Times New Roman, Arial, Georgia) for maximum compatibility, or accept that custom fonts may not appear on all devices.

