## Frequently Asked Questions

### Does DOCX to EPUB conversion lose formatting?

Some formatting is lost because DOCX is fixed-layout and EPUB is reflowable. Headings, bold, italic, lists, and paragraphs transfer well. Complex elements like text boxes, multi-column layouts, and custom WordArt may not. Preparing your DOCX properly minimizes losses.

### Can I convert DOCX to EPUB on Mac?

Yes. converter-epub.com works in any browser on Mac. Calibre also runs natively on macOS.

### Can I convert DOCX to EPUB on my phone?

Yes. converter-epub.com works on mobile browsers. For more complex conversions, Calibre Companion (iOS/Android) lets you manage Calibre libraries and send books to your device from anywhere.

### Is there a way to edit the EPUB after conversion?

Yes. [Sigil](https://sigil-ebook.com/) is a free, open-source EPUB editor for Mac and Windows. It lets you inspect and edit the underlying EPUB HTML/CSS directly.

### How do I send the EPUB to my Kindle?

**Via Calibre:** Connect your Kindle via USB, select the EPUB in Calibre, and click the device icon to send it. Calibre handles the MOBI/AZW3 conversion automatically.

**Via email:** Send the EPUB as an attachment to your Kindle's email address (found in your Amazon account settings). Amazon converts it to Kindle format during delivery.

